== Sweet Potato Fries ==

Preheat your #oven{} to 210°C.

Pop the @sweet potato fries{250%g} on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer.

Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{18-20%minutes}. Turn halfway 
through cooking.

== Prep ==

Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim the @green beans{150%g} then chop in half.

Zest and halve the @lime{1/2}.

== Limey Mayo ==

In a #small bowl{} mix the @mayonnaise{1%tbsp}, half the lime zest and half the 
lime juice.

Stir well and set aside.

== Mexican Spiced Cod ==

Line a baking tray with #parchment paper{}.

Put the @cod fillets{2} on the tray, drizzle over a little @oil{} and season 
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Evenly coat the top of the cod with the @Mexican Spice{1%tsp}.

Bake the fish on the middle shelf of your oven until cooked through, 
~{7-9%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

== Green Beans ==

Meanwhile, heat a splash of @oil{} in #medium sized frying pan{} on a high 
heat.

When hot add the beans.

Cook until the beans start to char, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add a splash of @water{}, cover the pan with a #lid{} or some #tin foil{} and cook 
until the beans are tender, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

Stir in the garlic and remaining lime zest and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Remove from the heat.

== To Serve ==

Share the beans between your plates.

Serve the sweet potato chips on the side.

Place the fish on top of the beans.

Serve with the lime mayo.

Enjoy!